The test of the 10-seater armored car "Novator" with the Ukrainian BM "TAVRIYA-14.5" was successfully carried out by LLC "Ukrainian Bronetechnika".

"TAVRIA-14.5" is a remote-controlled turret armed with a 14.5-mm machine gun (KPVT).

The main characteristics of the turret:
- BC with 200 cartridges;
- high-quality stabilization system;
- the ability to capture and accompany targets;
- detection range up to 5 km day and night.
- STANAG equipment protection level 1.

Forwarded from: Russian Embassy in Belarus
Boris Gryzlov took part in a meeting of the High-Level Group of the Council of Ministers of the Union State. The event took place in Minsk on March 12 with the participation of the Secretary of State of the Union State Dmitry Mezentsev, representatives of the relevant ministries and departments of the Russian Federation and the Republic of Belarus, as well as the Governor of the Smolensk region Vasily Anokhin. Deputy Chairman of the Russian Government Alexey Overchuk emphasized: • The economies of Russia and Belarus are growing at a faster rate than the economies of the European Union, which imposed illegal sanctions against us;

• the volume of accumulated investments in the Belarusian economy from Russia at the end of last year grew by 6.7% and reached almost $2.9 billion;

• the share of payments in national currencies within the Union State is 92%;

• we create products with high added value that can compete in foreign markets;

• as part of the import substitution policy, from March 2022 to February 2024, companies from 72 constituent entities of the Russian Federation concluded 5,236 foreign trade contracts with Belarusian partners. Read more
